        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1510356-laura?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer60590961" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14394186796691177582">It pains me to give anything by Sharon Kay Penman fewer than 4 or 5 stars, because she&apos;s one of my favorite authors. But this book just didn&apos;t fascinate me like her others did. Usually I am completely engrossed by her writing, but I never really felt a connection to these characters. It&apos;s an interesting story--Eleanor of Aquitaine and Henry II and the murder of Thomas Becket--but for some reason I never really got into it. I just don&apos;t think it&apos;s as well written as some of her other books. </span>
  <span id="freeText14394186796691177582" style="display:none">It pains me to give anything by Sharon Kay Penman fewer than 4 or 5 stars, because she's one of my favorite authors. But this book just didn't fascinate me like her others did. Usually I am completely engrossed by her writing, but I never really felt a connection to these characters. It's an interesting story--Eleanor of Aquitaine and Henry II and the murder of Thomas Becket--but for some reason I never really got into it. I just don't think it's as well written as some of her other books. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14394186796691177582" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
